{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":11878,"name":"","username":"JTippetts","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jtippetts/{size}/357_2.png","created_at":"2016-04-28T19:00:57.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eFor awhile, I‚Äôve noticed that when I enable shadows on my scene‚Äôs directional lights, I get banding and moire patterns on many surfaces:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://i.imgur.com/YgYURBI.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"251\" height=\"249\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"http://i.imgur.com/4NfO2YC.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"183\" height=\"178\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cimg src=\"http://i.imgur.com/20ffItg.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"188\" height=\"175\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt occurs even on flat, non-normal-mapped surfaces (such as the Siegebreaker‚Äôs hammer in the third pic).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe banding goes away if I disable shadows, so I‚Äôm sure that there is some tweaking I can do. Sadly, I don‚Äôt really understand the shadow process, so I‚Äôm not sure exactly which parameters to tweak or what values to shoot for. Changing things at random doesn‚Äôt really seem to get me anywhere, and the documentation isn‚Äôt really very descriptive about exactly what changes I can expect from tweaking which parameters. I‚Äôm guessing I need to modify Bias and/or Focus parameters. Can anyone point me in the right direction?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:06.291Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":44,"reads":16,"readers_count":15,"score":223.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1988,"topic_slug":"moire-patterns-and-artifacts-with-directional-lights","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":30,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":11879,"name":"","username":"rasteron","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rasteron/{size}/55_2.png","created_at":"2016-04-28T21:47:19.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI had this problem before. It‚Äôs the camera far distance and bias so try playing around with those values. I‚Äôd focus more on bias if you could not change your far distance due to some game visual reasons. If you‚Äôre also working on an isometric camera then decreasing the far distance a bit would not be a problem.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:06.353Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":16,"readers_count":15,"score":3.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1988,"topic_slug":"moire-patterns-and-artifacts-with-directional-lights","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":54,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":11926,"name":"","username":"Enhex","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/enhex/{size}/81_2.png","created_at":"2016-05-02T11:17:24.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eImplementing Shadow Map Normal Offset Bias could virtually solve it.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/shadow-map-normal-offset-bias/1904/1\"\u003etopic1991.html\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e